<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sverigetopplistan.se/chart/41?dspy=2020&dspp=13|title=Veckolista Singlar, vecka 13|publisher=[[Sverigetopplistan]]|accessdate=March 28, 2020}}</ref>\n| 33\n|-\n{{single chart|Switzerland|25|artist=Surfaces|song=Sunday Best|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 20, 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|UK|36|date=20200327|rowheader=true|accessdate=March 28, 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Billboardhot100|38|artist=Surfaces|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 21, 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Billboardadultpopsongs|25|artist=Surfaces|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 20, 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Billboardpopsongs|18|artist=Surfaces|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 20, 2020}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| US [[Rolling Stone Top 100|''Rolling Stone'' Top 100]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/charts/songs/2020-03-13/|title=Top 100 Songs|work=[[Rolling Stone]]|accessdate=April 2, 2020}}</ref>\n| 61\n|}\n\n== Certifications ==\n{{Certification Table Top}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=New Zealand|artist=Surfaces|title=Sunday Best|award=Gold|type=single|relyear=2019|relmonth=01|recent=website|id=4832|accessdate=March 15, 2020}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=United States|title=Sunday Best|artist=Surfaces|award=Gold|type=single|relyear=2019|certyear=2020|accessdate=March 15, 2020}}\n{{Certification Table Bottom}}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:2019 songs]]\n[[Category:2020 singles]]\n[[Category:TikTok songs]]\n\n{{2020s-song-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox song\n| name       = Sunday Best\n| type       = single\n| artist     = Surfaces\n| album      = Where the Light Is\n| released   = January 8, 2019\n| genre      = <!-- Please source genres -->\n| length     = 2:39\n| label      = {{hlist|TenThousand Projects|[[Caroline Records|Caroline]]}}\n| writer     = {{hlist|Forrest Frank|Colin Padalecki}}\n| producer   = {{hlist|Forrest Frank|Colin Padalecki}}\n| prev_title = Shine on Top\n| prev_year  = 2018\n| next_title = Palm Trees\n| next_year  = 2019\n| misc       = {{external music video|type=single|{{YouTube|83KqwEEGw4|\"Sunday Best\"}}}}\n}}\n\"'''Sunday Best'''\" is a song by American [[electro-pop]] duo Surfaces, composed of Forrest Frank and Colin Padalecki. The song was released by TenThousand Projects and [[Caroline Records]] on the duo's second album ''Where the Light Is'' on January 8, 2019. The song was re-released as Surfaces' lead single off their third album ''Horizons'' on February 28, 2020''.'' The song's music video was released on July 11, 2019 and it shows the duo turning a boring office to a party place.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.broadwayworld.com/bwwmusic/article/Surfaces-Shares-New-Music-Video-For-SUNDAY-BEST-20190711|title=Surfaces Shares New Music Video For SUNDAY BEST|date=July 11, 2019|website=[[BroadwayWorld]]|access-date=March 15, 2020}}</ref> The song is believed to have gained popularity in late February 2020 on the online-video sharing platform [[TikTok]] for its lyric \"Feeling good, like I should\",<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/business/branding/8551350/flighthouse-republic-records-partner-tiktok-series-certified-superfan|title=Flighthouse and Republic Records Partner on New TikTok Series 'Certified Superfan'|last=Eggertsen|first=Chris|date=February 19, 2020|website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|url-status=live|access-date=March 15, 2020}}</ref> before it was released for radio airplay in early March 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200302133607/https://www.allaccess.com/top40-mainstream/future-releases|title=Top 40/M Future Releases|date=March 3, 2020|website=[[All Access]]|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200302133607/https://www.allaccess.com/top40-mainstream/future-releases|archive-date=March 2, 2020|access-date=March 15, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.top-charts.com/s/sunday-best-surfaces|title=Sunday Best by Surfaces|website=Top-Charts.com|access-date=March 15, 2020}}</ref> The song peaked in the Top 40 in Australia, Canada, Norway, Ireland, New Zealand, the United Kingdom and the United States, as well as the top 100 in Switzerland, Germany and Sweden.\n\n== Live performances ==\nSurfaces made their late-night television debut when they performed the song on ''[[Late Night with Seth Meyers]]'' on March 2, 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://headlineplanet.com/home/2020/03/03/surfaces-perform-on-late-night-with-seth-meyers-first-look/|title=Surfaces Perform \"Sunday Best\" On \"Late Night With Seth Meyers\"|last=Cantor|first=Brian|date=March 3, 2020|website=Headline Planet|access-date=March 15, 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Charts ==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2020)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br />position\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Australia ([[ARIA Charts|ARIA]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ariacharts.com.au/charts/singles-chart|title=ARIA Australian Top 50 Singles|publisher=[[Australian Recording Industry Association]]|date=April 20, 2020|accessdate=April 18, 2020}}</ref>\n| 10\n|-\n{{single chart|Austria|51|artist=Surfaces|song=Sunday Best|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 22, 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Flanders|15|artist=Surfaces|song=Sunday Best|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 4, 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Wallonia|24|artist=Surfaces|song=Sunday Best|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 17, 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Canada|8|artist=Surfaces|rowheader=true|accessdate=March 31, 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Czechdigital|9|year=2020|week=14|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 7, 2020}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Denmark ([[Tracklisten]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://hitlisten.nu/default.asp?w=13&y=2020&list=t40|title=Track Top-40 Uge 13, 2020|publisher=[[Hitlisten]]|accessdate=April 8, 2020}}</ref>\n| 19\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Estonia ([[Eesti Tipp-40]])<ref name=\"estonianchart\">{{Cite web|url=https://ekspress.delfi.ee/areen/eesti-tipp-40-muusikas-dua-lipa-keeras-the-weekndil-kaela-kahekorra?id=89479383|title=Eesti Tipp-40 Muusikas: Dua Lipa keeras The Weekndil kaela kahekorra|language=Estonian|last=Nestor|first=Siim|website=[[Eesti Ekspress]]|date=April 7, 2020|accessdate=April 9, 2020}}</ref>\n| 18\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| France ([[Syndicat National de l'\u00c9dition Phonographique|SNEP]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://snepmusique.com/les-tops/le-top-de-la-semaine/top-albums/?semaine=16?&annee=2020&categorie=Top%20Singles|title=Top Singles (Week 16, 2020)|publisher=[[Syndicat National de l'\u00c9dition Phonographique]]|language=French|accessdate=April 21, 2020}}</ref>\n| 29\n|-\n{{single chart|Germany2|50|songid=1890835|artist=Surfaces|song=Sunday Best|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 17, 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Hungarystream|25|year=2020|week=14|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 10, 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Ireland4|20|date=20200417|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 18, 2020}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Italy ([[Federazione Industria Musicale Italiana|FIMI]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fimi.it/top-of-the-music/classifiche.kl#/charts/3/2020/16|title=Top Singoli \u2013 Classifica settimanale WK 16|publisher=[[Federazione Industria Musicale Italiana]]|language=Italian|accessdate=April 18, 2020}}</ref>\n| 49\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Lithuania ([[AGATA (organization)|AGATA]])<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.agata.lt/lt/naujienos/savaites-klausomiausi-2020w11/|title=2020 11-os savait\u0117s klausomiausi (TOP 100)|publisher=[[AGATA (organization)|AGATA]]|language=Lithuanian|accessdate=March 16, 2020}}</ref>\n| 17\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Malaysia ([[Recording Industry Association of Malaysia|RIM]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/RecordingIndustryMalaysia/photos/pcb.3374338752593471/3374338659260147/?type=3&theater|title=Top 20 Most Streamed International & Domestic Singles In Malaysia|work=[[Recording Industry Association of Malaysia]]|publisher=Recording Industry Association of Malaysia|accessdate=April 12, 2020}}</ref>\n| 13\n|-\n{{single chart|Dutch10