{"title_page": "Avneet Kaur", "text_new": "{{short description|Indian television and film actress}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2019}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=September 2015}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Avneet Kaur\n| image              = Avneet Kaur.jpg\n| caption            =\n| birth_date         = <!--Birthdate must be attributed to a reliable published source with an established reputation for fact-checking. No blogs. No IMDb. No public records. See WP:BLPPRIVACY-->\n| birth_place        = <!--Must be attributed to a reliable published source with an established reputation for fact-checking. No blogs, no IMDb.-->\n| residence          = <!--Must be attributed to a reliable published source with an established reputation for fact-checking. No blogs, no IMDb.-->\n| nationality        = [[India]]n\n| occupation         = {{ubl|Actress|dancer}}\n| years_active       = 2010 \u2013 present\n| known_for          = ''[[Dance India Dance Li'l Masters]]''<br />''[[Chandra Nandini]]''<br />''[[Aladdin - Naam Toh Suna Ho \nMOTHER               = Sonia nandra\nFATHER               = amandeep nandra\nSIBLING              = Jaijeet singh\n'''Avneet Kaur''' is an Indian actress.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/hindi/from-siddharth-nigam-jannat-zubair-rehmani-to-avneet-kaur-young-brigade-take-over-tv/photostory/66639384.cms|title=From Siddharth Nigam, Jannat Zubair Rehmani to Avneet Kaur: Young brigade take over TV|date=15 November 2018|website=The Times of India}}</ref> She started her career with ''[[Dance India Dance Li'l Masters]]'' as a contestant. She then participated in ''[[Dance Ke Superstars]]''. Kaur made her acting debut with ''Meri Maa'', playing the character Jhilmil. Later, she was part of ''Tedhe Hain Par Tere Mere Hain''.\n\nIn June 2012, she participated in ''[[Jhalak Dikhhla Jaa|Jhalak Dikhhla Jaa 5]]''. In 2012, she was seen in ''[[Savitri - EK Prem Kahani|Savitri]]'', as Young Rajkumari Damyanti and in 2013 as Young Pakhi in ''[[Ek Mutthi Aasmaan (TV series)|Ek Mutthi Aasmaan]]''. Kaur started her film career as a child actor with the 2014 film ''[[Mardaani]]'' with the role of Meera. She then portrayed the role of Khushi in ''[[Hamari Sister Didi]]''.\n\nIn 2017, she portrayed the role of Princess Charumati in ''[[Chandra Nandini]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.abplive.in/television/avneet-kaur-joins-chandra-nandni-opposite-siddharth-nigam-563694/amp|title=Avneet Kaur joins 'Chandra Nandni' opposite Siddharth Nigam|website=ABP Live|language=en-US|access-date=22 August 2018|date=10 August 2017}}</ref> She is playing Princess Yasmine in [[SAB TV]]'s ''[[Aladdin - Naam Toh Suna Hoga]]'' with [[Siddharth Nigam]] since 2018.\n\n==Career==\nKaur began her career with [[Zee TV]]'s dance show ''[[Dance India Dance Li'l Masters]].''<ref name=\"Avneet-Kaur-in-Life-OKs-Savitri\">{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tv/Avneet-Kaur-in-Life-OKs-Savitri/articleshow/16968373.cms |title=Avneet Kaur in Life OK's Savitri |work=The Times of India |date=26 October 2012 |accessdate=16 September 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"Avneet-Kaur-on-Jhalak\">{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/hindi/Darsheel-to-pair-up-with-Avneet-Kaur-on-Jhalak/articleshow/13851166.cms |title=Darsheel to pair up with Avneet Kaur on Jhalak |work=The Times of India |date=5 June 2012 |accessdate=16 September 2015}}</ref> She got eliminated before the semi-finals.<ref name=\"small-size-wonders\">{{cite web|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/chandigarh/small-size-wonders/article1-1151008.aspx |title=Small-size wonders |work=Hindustantimes |date=14 November 2013 |accessdate=16 September 2015}}</ref> She then participated in ''[[Dance Ke Superstars]]'', where she joined the team of \"Dance Challengers\".<ref name=\"bollywood-debut\">{{cite web|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/chandigarh/kid-from-jalandhar-to-make-bollywood-debut/article1-1249240.aspx |title=Kid from Jalandhar to make Bollywood debut |work=Hindustantimes |date=7 August 2014 |accessdate=16 September 2015}}</ref> Kaur made her acting debut in 2012 with [[Life OK]]'s ''[[List of programs broadcast by Life OK|Meri Maa]]''<ref name=\"Avneet-Kaur-in-Tedhe-Hain\" /> where she played the role of Jhilmil.<ref name=\"bollywood-debut\" /> Then, she was seen in [[SAB TV]]'s ''Tedhe Hain Par Tere Mere Hain''.<ref name=\"Avneet-Kaur-in-Tedhe-Hain\">{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/hindi/Avneet-Kaur-in-Tedhe-Hain-Par-Tere-Mere-Hain/articleshow/14209130.cms |title=Avneet Kaur in Tedhe Hain Par Tere Mere Hain |work=The Times of India |date=17 June 2012 |accessdate=16 September 2015}}</ref> She then participated in the [[Colors TV]]'s celebrity dance reality show ''[[Jhalak Dikhhla Jaa]]'',<ref name=\"Avneet-Kaur-in-Tedhe-Hain\" /> where she was a contestant with [[Darsheel Safary]]. She was eliminated in August.<ref name=\"Avneet-Kaur-on-Jhalak\" /><ref name=\"jaltrib\">{{cite web|url=http://www.tribuneindia.com/2012/20120618/jaltrib.htm|title=The Tribune, Chandigarh, India - JALANDHAR PLUS|date=|work=Tribuneindia|accessdate=16 September 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=Bollywood Hungama |url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/more/videos/view/id/1557315 |title=Darsheel- Avneet's Hip-Hop Performance |work=Bollywood Hungama |date= |accessdate=16 September 2015}}</ref> Later, Kaur was featured in [[Life OK]]'s ''[[Savitri (TV series)|Savitri]]'', where she played the role of Rajkumari Damyanti.<ref name=\"Avneet-Kaur-in-Life-OKs-Savitri\"/> In August 2013, Kaur played the role of Pakhi in [[Zee TV]]'s ''[[Ek Mutthi Aasmaan (TV series)|Ek Mutthi Aasmaan]]''.<ref name=\"the-little-telly-star\">{{cite web|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/chunk-ht-ui-punjabsectionpage-dontmiss/the-little-telly-star/article1-1112636.aspx|title=The little telly star|date=25 August 2013|work=Hindustantimes|accessdate=16 September 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"Avneet-in-Aasman\">{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tv/Avneet-Kaur-Jasmine-Avasia-in-Ek-Mutthi-Aasman/articleshow/21934076.cms |title=Avneet Kaur & Jasmine Avasia in Ek Mutthi Aasman |work=The Times of India |date=20 August 2013 |accessdate=16 September 2015}}</ref> She also appeared in [[ZeeQ]]'s news bulletin titled, ''[[Zee Entertainment Enterprises|The Weekly Rap]]''.<ref name=\"small-size-wonders\" /> Kaur has featured in various advertisements including [[Hindustan Unilever#Brands|Clinic Plus]], [[Maggi]] and [[Lifebuoy (soap)#References in popular culture|Lifebuoy Handwash]].<ref name=\"small-size-wonders\"/>\n\nKaur started her filming career in 2014 with [[Pradeep Sarkar]]'s ''[[Mardaani]]''.<ref name=\"bollywood-debut\"/>\n\nIn September 2014, she played the role of Khushi in [[Sony Pal]]'s ''[[Hamari Sister Didi]]''.<ref name=\"trouble-in-Hamari-Sister\">{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/hindi/Double-trouble-in-Hamari-Sister-Didi/articleshow/45283836.cms |title=Double trouble in Hamari Sister Didi |work=The Times of India |date=26 November 2014 |accessdate=16 September 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"studies-and-acting\">{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/hindi/How-Avneet-Kaur-Kohli-balances-studies-and-acting/articleshow/43817187.cms |title=How Avneet Kaur Kohli balances studies and acting |work=The Times of India |date=30 September 2014 |accessdate=16 September 2015}}</ref> In 2017, Kaur played the role of Charumati in ''[[Chandra Nandini]]''. Since 2018, she is seen as Princess [[Jasmine (Disney)|Yasmine]] in [[SAB TV]]'s ''[[Aladdin - Naam Toh Suna Hoga]].''\n\n==Filmography==\n===Television===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Notes\n! Ref.\n|-\n| 2010\n|''[[Dance India Dance Li'l Masters]]''\n| rowspan=\"3\" | Contestant\n|\n|\n|-\n| 2011\n| ''[[Dance Ke Superstars]]''\n|\n|\n|-\n| 2012\n| ''[[Jhalak Dikhhla Jaa (season 5)|Jhalak Dikhhla Jaa 5]]''\n|\n|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tellychakkar.com/tv/tv-news/darsheel-safary-and-avneet-kaur-get-eliminated-jhalak |title=Darsheel Safary and Avneet Kaur get eliminated from Jhalak |work=Tellychakkar |date=1 September 2012 |accessdate=16 September 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2011\u20132012\n| ''[[Meri Maa (Indian TV series)|Meri Maa]]''\n| Jhilmil\n|\n|\n|-\n| 2012\n| ''Tedhe Hain Par Tere Mere Hain''\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 2013\n| ''[[Savitri - EK Prem Kahani|Savitri]]''\n| Young Damyanti\n| rowspan=\"3\" | Child Artist\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Ek Mutthi Aasmaan (TV series)|Ek Mutthi Aasmaan]]''\n| Young Pakhi\n|\n|-\n| 2014\u20132015\n| ''[[Hamari Sister Didi]]''\n| Khushi\n|\n|-\n| 2015\n| ''Twistwala Love''\n| Raina Mehra\n|\n|\n|-\n| 2017\n| ''[[Chandra Nandini]]''\n| Crown Princess Charumati\n| Negative Role\n|\n|-\n| 2018\u2013present\n| ''[[Aladdin - Naam Toh Suna Hoga]]''\n| Sultana Yasmine\n| Lead role\n|<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/television/siddharth-nigam-avneet-kaur-aladdin-5174285/|title=Siddharth Nigam and Avneet Kaur in SAB TV's fantasy drama Aladdin|date=12 May 2018|work=The Indian Express|access-date=7 August 2018|language=en-US}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2019\n| ''[[Kitchen Champion]]''\n| Guest\n|\n|\n|}\n\n===Films===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Film\n! Role\n! Notes\n|-\n| 2014\n| ''[[Mardaani]]''\n| Meera\n| Debut\n|-\n| 2017\n| ''Brunie''\n| Shivani\n|\n|-\n| 2017\n| ''[[Qarib Qarib Singlle]]''\n| Teenage Girl at the Clothing Store\n|\n|-\n| 2018\n| ''EKTA''\n| Ekta (child)\n|\n|-\n|2019\n|''[[Mardaani 2]]''\n|Meera\n|\n|}\n\n===Web series===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Platform\n! Notes\n|-\n| rowspan=2|2018\n| ''Babbar Ka Tabbar''\n| rowspan=2|Nikki Babbar\n| rowspan=2|[[Zee5|Zee 5]]\n|<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.dnaindia.com/television/report-zee5-premieres-babbar-ka-tabbar-2627925|title=ZEE5 premieres 'Babbar Ka Tabbar'|date=22 June 2018|work=dna|access-date=3 September 2018|language=en-