h Kumar Mishra\n|[[Sanskrit literature|Sanskrit Literature]]\n|}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+AWARDED BOOKS PUBLISHED IN THE YEARS -1985,1986 & 1987\t\t\t\n|-\n! #\n! Book\n! Author\n! Category of Books \n|-\n|123\n|Aji Kali Paaradina\n|[[Rajendra Prasad Das]]\n|[[Novel]]\n|-\n|124\n|Nachiketara Hata\n|Uttam Kumar Pradhan\t\n|[[Short Story]]\n|-\n|125\n|Dhana Saunta Jhia\n|Hrusikesh Mallick\n|[[Verse (poetry)|Verses]]-[[Poems]]\n|-\n|126\n|Janasevak\n|Prasanna Kumar Mishra\n|[[One-act play|Plays - One Act Plays]] \n|-\n|127\n|Matrupuja Mandap\n|Sadasiba Mishra\n|[[Essays]] - [[Criticism]]\n|-\n|128\n|Smruti O Anubhuti\n|Nilamani Routray\n|[[Biography|Biographies]]-[[Travel literature|Travelogue]]\n|-\n|129\n|Bhuin Tale Tale\n|Durga Prasad Patnaik\n|[[Children\u2019s literature|Children\u2019s Literature]]\n|-\n|130\n|Jagannathastottarsatakam\n|Sudarshan Acharya\n|[[Sanskrit literature|Sanskrit Literature]]\n|}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+AWARDED BOOKS PUBLISHED IN THE YEARS -1986,1987 & 1988\n|-\n! #\n! Book\n! Author\n! Category of Books \n|-\n|131\n|Banhi Balay\n|Madan Mohan Mishra\n|[[Novel]] \n|-\n|132\n|Manwantarar Manab\n|Rajkishore Ray\n|[[Short Story]]\n|-\n|133\n|Anantsayan\n|Shakuntala Devi\n|Verses-[[Poems]] \n|-\n|134\n|Ei Je Surya Uein\n|Bijay Kumar Satpathy\n|[[One-act play|Plays - One Act Plays]]  \n|-\n|135\n|Raktatirtha Eram\n|Jagannath Patnaik\n|[[Essays]] -[[Criticism]] \n|-\n|136\n|Karagarar Kahani\n|Surendra Nath Dwivedi\n|[[Biography]]- [[Travel literature|Travelogue]] \n|-\n|137\n|Gapudi O Pakudi\n|Nadiya Bihari Mohanty\n|[[Children\u2019s literature]]\n|-\n|138\n|Surendra Charita Maha Kavyam\n|Digambar Mohapatra\n|[[Sanskrit literature|Sanskrit Literature]]\n|}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+AWARDED BOOKS PUBLISHED IN THE YEARS -1987,1988 &1989\t\t\t\n|-\n! #\n! Book\n! Author\n! Category of Books \n|-\n|139\n|Janharati\n|Yasodhara Mishra\n|[[Short Story]]  \n|-\n|140\n|Kaniska Kaniska\n|[[Jagadish Mohanty]]\n|[[Novel]] \n|-\n|141\n|Ipsita Krodha\n|Asutosh Parida\n|[[Verse (poetry)|Verses]]-[[Poems]] \n|-\n|142\n|Samudra Manthan\n|Gopal Chandra Patnaik\n|[[One-act play|Plays - One Act Plays]]  \n|-\n|143\n|Ho Bhagate\n|Subodh Patnaik\n|[[One-act play|Plays - One Act Plays]]  \n|-\n|144\n|Sri Jagannath Tatwa\n|Gopinath Mohapatra\n|[[Essays]] - [[Criticism]] \n|-\n|145\n|Patalpurir Halchal\n|Guru Prasad Mohanty\n|[[Biography]]- [[Travel literature|Travelogue]] \n|-\n|146\n|Rajar Swapna\n|Birendra Kumar Samantray\n|[[Children\u2019s literature]]\n|-\n|147\n|Rutam\n|[[Keshab Chandra Dash]]\n|[[Sanskrit literature|Sanskrit Literature]]\n|}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+AWARDED BOOKS PUBLISHED IN THE YEARS -1988,1989 & 1990\t\t\t\n|-\n! #\n! Book\n! Author\n! Category of Books \n|-\n|148\n|Durg Patanar Bela\n|Padmja Pal\n|[[Novel]] \n|-\n|149\n|Devdasi\n|Bijayini Das\n|[[Novel]] \n|-\n|150\n|Prachakshyu\n|Bijay Krushna Mohanty\n|[[Short Story]] \n|-\n|151\n|Sabaricharya\n|Bansidhar Sadangi\n|[[Verse (poetry)|Verses]]-[[Poems]] \n|-\n|152\n|Bhor Akash\n|Nityanand Nayak\n|[[Verse (poetry)|Verses]]-[[Poems]] \n|-\n|153\n|Asra Khoji Buluthiba Iswar\n|Narayan Sahoo\n|[[One-act play|Plays - One Act Plays]]  \n|-\n|154\n|Bhinna Samay Bhinna Drusti\n|Niladri Bhusan Harichandan\n|[[Essays]] - [[Criticism]] \n|-\n|155\n|Sanskruta Sahityar Itihas\n|Harekrushna Satpathy\n|[[Essays]] - [[Criticism]] \n|-\n|157\n|Bajare Baja\n|Ram Prasad Mohanty\n|[[Children\u2019s literature]]\n|-\n|158\n|Abhinab Kabitabalih\n|Narayan Rath\n|[[Sanskrit literature|Sanskrit Literature]]\n|-\n|\n|\n|\n|''to be continued....''\n|}\n\n==See also==\n*[[Sahitya Akademi|Sahitya Akademi Award]]\n*[[Jnanpith Award]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://orissa.gov.in/e-magazine/orissaannualreference/ORA-2005/pdf/orissa_sahitya_academy.pdf Orissa Sahitya Academy Award winners]\n\n[[Category:Awards established in 1957]]\n[[Category:Indian literary awards]]\n[[Category:Odia literature]]\n", "text_old": "{{distinguish|List of Sahitya Akademi Award winners for Oriya}}\n{{Infobox award\n| name = Odisha Sahitya Akademi Award<br>{{native name|or|\u0b13\u0b21\u0b3c\u0b3f\u0b36\u0b3e \u0b38\u0b3e\u0b39\u0b3f\u0b24\u0b4d\u0b5f \u0b0f\u0b15\u0b3e\u0b21\u0b47\u0b2e\u0b3f \u0b2a\u0b41\u0b30\u0b38\u0b4d\u0b15\u0b3e\u0b30|italics=off}}\n| image = \n| image_size = \n| alt = \n| caption = \n| subheader = Award for contributions to [[Literature]]\n| description = Literary award in [[India]] \n| sponsor = [[Odisha Sahitya Akademi]]\n| firstawarded = 1957-58 \n| lastawarded = \n| reward = \n| former name = \n| website = {{URL|http://www.orissaculture.gov.in/osa.asp}}\n| previous = \n| next =  \n}}\n\n'''Odisha Sahitya Akademi''' ({{Lang-or|\u0b13\u0b21\u0b3c\u0b3f\u0b36\u0b3e \u0b38\u0b3e\u0b39\u0b3f\u0b24\u0b4d\u0b5f \u0b0f\u0b15\u0b3e\u0b21\u0b47\u0b2e\u0b3f \u0b2a\u0b41\u0b30\u0b38\u0b4d\u0b15\u0b3e\u0b30}} is an institution established in 1957 in [[Odisha]]<ref name=\"Bureau 2016\">{{cite web | last=Bureau | first=TT | title=80-year journey of struggle & success | website=Telegraph India | date=2016-04-01 | url=https://www.telegraphindia.com/states/odisha/80-year-journey-of-struggle-amp-success/cid/1504744 | access-date=2019-07-08}}</ref> for active promotion of [[Odia language]] and literature.<ref name=\"osa\">{{cite web | url=http://www.orissaculture.gov.in/osa.asp | title=Odisha Sahitya Academy | publisher=Department of Culture, Government of Odisha | accessdate=March 9, 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Awards==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+ AWARDED BOOKS PUBLISHED IN 1957 & 1958\n|-\n! #\n! Book\n! Author\n! Category of Books \n|-\n|1\n|Dilip \n|Upendra Mohanty \n|[[Verse (poetry)|Verses-Poems]]\t\n|-\n|2\n|Swarna Yugar Sandhya \n|Gyanindra Burma \n|[[One-act play|Plays - One Act Plays]]  \n|-\n|3\n|Agni Parikshya \n|Bhanja Kishor Patnaik \n|[[One-act play|Plays - One Act Plays]]  \n|-\n|4\n|Vyasa Kabi Phakir Mohan \n| [[Natabar Samantray]]\n|[[Criticism]] \n|-\n|5\n|Vedas Manusya Kruta Ki ? \n|Priyabrat Das \n|[